definitions.definition: A second-year undergraduate student in a college or university , or a second-year student in a four-year secondary school or high school .
examples: She was very mature for a sophomore and had several friends who were juniors or even seniors.
The filly had looked promising as a sophomore , but concerns over her health had prompted the owner to pull her from the season’s early races.

main_definition: ( US , Philippines ) A second-year undergraduate student in a college or university , or a second-year student in a four-year secondary school or high school .
